5.what is responsive web application in python?
When you build a web app using Python (Flask, Django, FastAPI, etc.):
Python handles the server, logic, database, and routes.
The web browser displays HTML + CSS.
CSS frameworks like Bootstrap, Tailwind CSS, or media queries make the layout responsive.
So, the responsiveness comes from frontend design, but the app itself is powered by Python 
A responsive Python web app typically includes:
1.Flexible layouts
2.Media queries

6.what is conflict in github?
A conflict in GitHub occurs when two branches make different changes to the same part of a file, and Git cannot automatically merge the changes. Common scenarios include editing the same line of code, or one branch editing a file while another deletes it. To resolve a conflict, you must manually intervene by identifying the conflicting code, deciding which changes to keep, and then committing the merged changes.  
What causes a conflict
Editing the same line: Two different branches modify the exact same line of code, and Git doesn't know which version is correct. 
Editing vs. Deleting: One branch modifies a file, while another branch deletes the same file. 
Renaming vs. Editing: A file is renamed in one branch but modified in another. 


